@startuml seq-login-jwt
' Eòlas KMS — Login & JWT validation
' Source:
'   kosha-app/.../config/SecurityConfig.kt   (resource server + KeycloakJwtConverter)
'   kosha-identity/.../service/UserCreationService.kt   (provisioning, separate flow)
' Keycloak holds credentials; Kosha mirrors a UserProfile keyed by keycloakId.

title Sequence — Login &amp; JWT validation (OIDC Authorization Code + PKCE)

actor User
participant "kosha-web\n(SvelteKit)" as Web
participant "Keycloak 24" as KC
participant "Spring Security\nfilter chain" as Sec
participant "KeycloakJwtConverter" as Conv
participant "REST controller\n(@PreAuthorize)" as Ctrl
participant "UserProfileRepository" as Repo
database "PostgreSQL\n(ident.user_profile)" as PG

== Initial login ==
User -> Web : Visit kosha.example.com
Web -> User : Redirect to Keycloak\n(/auth, response_type=code, PKCE)
User -> KC : Enter credentials
KC --> User : Redirect back with ?code=...
User -> Web : /callback?code=...
Web -> KC : POST /token (code + verifier)
KC --> Web : {access_token, refresh_token, id_token}
Web -> Web : Store tokens (httpOnly cookie or memory)

== Authenticated API call ==
User -> Web : Click "Search documents"
Web -> Sec : GET /api/v1/search\nAuthorization: Bearer <access_token>
Sec -> KC : Fetch JWKS (cached)
Sec -> Sec : Validate signature, exp, iss, aud
Sec -> Conv : convert(jwt)
Conv -> Conv : authorities = roles.map { ROLE_$it }\nname = preferred_username
Conv --> Sec : JwtAuthenticationToken
Sec -> Ctrl : invoke handler
Ctrl -> Ctrl : @PreAuthorize hasAnyRole(...) check
Ctrl -> Repo : findByKeycloakId(jwt.subject)

alt UserProfile already exists
  Repo --> Ctrl : profile
else first call after admin provisioned in Keycloak only
  note right of Ctrl
    Edge case: out-of-band Keycloak users
    are not auto-mirrored here. The supported
    path is admin → POST /api/v1/users/provision,
    which creates Keycloak + UserProfile atomically
    via UserCreationService (separate flow).
  end note
end

Ctrl --> Web : 200 result
Web --> User : Render

== Token refresh (silent) ==
Web -> KC : POST /token\ngrant_type=refresh_token
KC --> Web : new access_token

== Failure paths ==
note over Sec, KC
  - Invalid signature / expired token → 401
  - Token valid but role missing → @PreAuthorize denies → 403
  - kosha.security.dev-bypass.enabled=true (dev only):
    a separate Order(0) filter chain skips JWT entirely
    for a fixed list of admin paths. Logs a loud banner
    on startup. NEVER set in production.
end note

@enduml
